                            <comment id="15081432" author="tilman" created="Mon, 4 Jan 2016 17:38:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The javadoc tells:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The returned BufferedImage shares the same data array as the original image.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some debug output:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;alphaRaster: ByteInterleavedRaster: width = 171 height = 142 #numDataElements 1 dataOff[0] = 2752&lt;br/&gt;
image size: 171 142&lt;br/&gt;
alphaRaster sample size: 343 284&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Don&apos;t know why I used &lt;tt&gt;alphaRaster.getSampleModel().getHeight()&lt;/tt&gt; instead of &lt;tt&gt;alphaRaster.getHeight()&lt;/tt&gt; in 2014, maybe copy and paste programming, although I don&apos;t see an &quot;inspiration URL&quot; in the code, which I usually add.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please test your code again with a -SNAPSHOT version and reopen if it doesn&apos;t work.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
